    <Folder>
      <name>Intelligence Summary</name>
      <Placemark>
        <name>AI Council Assessment</name>
        <styleUrl>#intel</styleUrl>
        <description>The synthesized analysis reveals a pronounced U.S. military posture characterized by high operational tempo and strategic concentration in the Indo-Pacific region. Ten carrier strike groups and amphibious ready groups are deployed in the Philippine Sea as part of Valiant Shield 2026 and Resolute Dragon 26 exercises, demonstrating an unprecedented level of power projection and allied coordination. This deployment, involving multiple carrier classes and amphibious assault ships, underscores a deliberate strategy to deter regional aggression, particularly in response to China&#39;s carrier operations and North Korea&#39;s naval expansion. Concurrently, ISR and strategic airlift operations—including E-3 Sentry AWACS flights over Europe and C-17 Globemaster III missions—highlight sustained global mobility and intelligence-gathering capabilities. The deployment of HH-60W Jolly Green II helicopters to East Africa further indicates a broadening counterterrorism and crisis response footprint. The data suggests a military posture balancing forward presence with rapid global deployment, emphasizing multi-domain readiness and allied interoperability. The absence of notable vessel movements outside the Philippine Sea and the concentration of training sorties in the continental U.S. reinforce the focus on Indo-Pacific deterrence and readiness.</description>
        <Point>
          <coordinates>0,0,0</coordinates>
        </Point>
      </Placemark>
    </Folder>
